---
import DefaultLayout from "../../layouts/default.astro";
---

<DefaultLayout title="Naviget Refund and Cancellation Policy">
    <div
        class="border-default p-6 mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl tracking-wider justify-around md:p-12"
    >
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl tracking-tight text-heading md:text-6xl">
            Naviget Refund and Cancellation Policy
        </h1>

        <p class="font-normal text-body mb-3">Effective Date: 21 April 2026</p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            This Refund and Cancellation Policy explains our policies regarding
            cancellations, refunds, and the resolution of disputes related to
            bookings and services made through Naviget.
        </p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            By using our Service, you agree to the terms set out in this Refund
            and Cancellation Policy.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">Definitions</h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            For the purposes of this Refund and Cancellation Policy:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Company (referred to as ‘the Company’, ‘We’, ‘Us’, or ‘Our’)
                refers to StepZero Labs Private Limited, Pavani Sreshta, Silver
                Spring Layout, Munnekollal, EPIP, Bangalore.
            </li>
            <li>
                Service refers to the platform, applications, and services
                provided by Naviget, accessible from https://naviget.in.
            </li>
            <li>
                User, You, or Your means the individual accessing or using the
                Service, or the company or legal entity on behalf of which such
                individual is accessing or using the Service.
            </li>
            <li>
                Booking refers to the transportation services (e.g., autos,
                taxis, cabs, bikes) and other mobility solutions booked through
                the Naviget platform.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">Cancellation Policy</h2>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">
            User-Initiated Cancellations
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Users may cancel a booking via the Naviget app before the
                driver/partner reaches the pickup point.
            </li>
            <li>
                Unless stated otherwise in the ride information when booking a
                ride on the platform, users won't be charged any cancellation
                fees if cancelled before 2 hours of pickup time.
            </li>
            <li>
                Unless stated otherwise in the ride information when booking a
                ride on the platform, cancellations made within 2 hours of
                pickup time will attract a cancellation fee of 50%.
            </li>
            <li>
                User will be charged 100% cancellation fee in case of no show or
                incorrect pickup location. Once boarded the cab no refund will
                be made due to change of plans.
            </li>
            <li>
                Repeated cancellations may lead to temporary or permanent
                suspension of your account.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">
            Driver/Partner-Initiated Cancellations
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                In the event we cancel the ride, Users will be notified
                immediately.
            </li>
            <li>
                Users will have the option to rebook another ride at no
                additional cost.
            </li>
            <li>
                We strive to minimize our cancellations and take strict actions
                against partners with repeated cancellations.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">Refund Policy</h2>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">Refund Eligibility</h3>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            Refunds are applicable in the following situations:
        </p>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                You were charged incorrectly due to a technical glitch or error.
            </li>
            <li>The service was not rendered despite successful payment.</li>
            <li>
                The driver did not arrive for a confirmed booking and you were
                charged.
            </li>
            <li>Any duplicate payments made due to technical issues.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">Refund Process</h3>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Refund requests must be raised via hello@naviget.in or through
                the in-app support chat within 24 hours of the incident.
            </li>
            <li>
                Refunds, once approved, will be processed within 7-10 business
                days to the original payment method.
            </li>
            <li>
                Naviget reserves the right to decline refund requests if they
                are found to be fraudulent, malicious, or in violation of our
                terms of service.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-heading text-xl mb-2 mt-4">Non-Refundable Charges</h3>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                Cancellation fees, waiting charges, and convenience fees are
                non-refundable unless otherwise decided on a case-by-case basis.
            </li>
            <li>
                Toll charges, parking charges and other mandatory charges once
                paid to respective authorities will not be refundable.
            </li>
            <li>
                Refunds are not applicable for delays caused due to traffic
                conditions, weather, or other unavoidable external factors.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">Dispute Resolution</h2>

        <ul class="list-disc list-inside md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            <li>
                For disputes regarding charges, Users can contact us at
                hello@naviget.in with booking details.
            </li>
            <li>
                We will investigate the matter and resolve disputes in a fair
                and transparent manner.
            </li>
            <li>
                The Company’s decision on disputes will be final and binding.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">
            Changes to This Refund and Cancellation Policy
        </h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            We may update this policy from time to time.
        </p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            The latest version will always be available at https://naviget.in
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-3xl mb-2 mt-4">Contact Us</h2>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            For any questions or concerns regarding this policy, please contact:
        </p>

        <p class="md:text-lg font-normal text-body">
            Email: hello@naviget.in Website: https://naviget.in
        </p>
    </div>
</DefaultLayout>
